race.comment: THINKING OF GERTY (10) resumes and has won 3/3 fresh. Brings strong metro form and owns an Echuca trial win. Maps well, and a bold run is likely. JAHANGIR (7) rides the speed and followed a nose defeat at Werribee this grade with a plainer effort at Seymour in a 62. He will skip across and has a senior hoop takes over. Comes out of a top metro stable and deserves another chance. Stablemate BLUE AKOYA (13) also races forward and spiked his figures again winning a Cranbourne Maiden heavily bet. She's sure to keep improving and Nugent stays aboard. CONDOR (1) is a leader who went close at Cranbourne. Peaks and the 3kg claim brings him into it.
